4. what is pthread_attach and pthread_join and difference
Ans:  Memory and system resources leak and in Over time → you may run out of resources
      When a thread finishes, its resources are not fully released & System accumulates "zombie threads"
      pthread_create failed: Resource temporarily unavailable
      Finished thread = still occupies: stack memory & thread descriptor
      Only pthread_join() frees these resources

      pthread_detach(tid); Automatically cleans up after thread exits
      ✔ Best for "fire-and-forget" tasks

      pthread_join(pid, NULL)  --> will block the main thread untill thread is joined
      pthread_detach(pid)  --> main process cannot be blocked.
